Lumpy skin disease, Israel
--------------------------
Information received on (and dated) 16 Dec 2012 from Dr Nadav Galon, director, Veterinary Services and Animal Health, Ministry of Agriculture and Rural Development, Bet Dagan, Israel

Summary
Report type: follow-up report No. 6
Date of start of the event: 01 Jul 2012
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 27 Jul 2012
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: November 2007
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: Lumpy skin disease virus
Nature of diagnosis: suspicion, clinical, laboratory (basic and advanced), necropsy
This event pertains to the whole country

New outbreaks (9)
[For the respective detailed information on each of the new outbreaks covered in this follow-up report, please refer to the source URL. The 9 outbreaks started between 1 Nov and 5 Dec 2012 in 6 grazing beef cattle herds and 3 housed dairy cattle farms, located in the subdistricts Golan, Tsefat, and Kineret, all in Hazafon (=North) district. - Mod.AS]

Summary of outbreaks:
Total outbreaks: 9
Total animals affected
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 4110 / 194 (incomplete information) / 7 / 8 / 0

Epidemiological comments: The disease continues to spread towards the south and west of the index outbreak. Lately, some dairy herds have been affected (small number of animals). Modified stamping out has been practiced in these herds (euthanasia of the symptomatic animals).

Control measures
Measures applied: control of arthropods, quarantine, movement control inside the country, screening, dipping/spraying, modified stamping out

Vaccination in response to the outbreak(s):
Administrative division / Species / Total vaccinated / Details
Hazafon / Cattle / 44 136 / Sheep pox vaccine (Jovac)

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: Virology Laboratory, Kimron Veterinary Institute (National laboratory)
Species / Test / Test date / Result
Cattle / polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 11 Dec 2012 / Positive

--
communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[As can be seen in the interactive map included in the current follow-up report (at the source URL), lumpy skin disease now covers the entire north eastern part of Israel's Hazafon (North) district, bordering Syria and Lebanon. The spread of the disease since July 2012, when the 1st 2 foci were recorded on the Syrian border in the Golan, will become apparent when comparing the current map with the one included in the initial report on 2 potbreaks, submitted 26 Jul 2012. It is available at http://tinyurl.com/c6ck5dv.

So far, 39 outbreaks have been officially reported to the OIE. - Mod.AS]
